                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Bankura, June 12: Prohibitory orders un- der Section 144 of the CrPC have been clamp-ed for a month in Bankuras Ranibandh, Raipur and Sarenga following violence involving supporters of the Peoples Committee Against Police Atrocities. The tribal resistance group had been creating trouble in the area to extend its clout beyond neighbouring Lalgarh and Jhargram.         
	Calcutta: Bengal has sought a Rs 500-crore advance from the national calamity fund to deal with the crisis caused by cyclone Aila.                                                                                                                                                                       
